#eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 NKANDLA - Former president Jacob Zuma and EFF leader Julius Malema met for tea at Nkandla on Friday. Malema reached out to Zuma on Twitter and suggested the meeting. A meeting between the leader of the EFF Julius Malema and former president Jacob Zuma and over some nice hot tea. Zuma hosted Malema at Nkandla where they met for four hours. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 The former president agreed, inviting Malema to his homestead in Northern KZN. The EFF tweeted pictures of the two leaders, shaking hands, not wearing marks or observing social distancing. Malema was accompanied by party member Dali Mpofu and spokesperson Vuyani Pambo. Zuma's allies, ANC NEC member Tony Yengeni and Ekurhuleni Mayor Mzwandile Masina were also there. When asked about the meeting, Pambo said it was "sweet and hot". Senior eNCA reporter Dasen Thathiah was at Nkandla. Watch the video above. Former president Jacob Zuma and EFF Leader Julius Malema seem to have put their differences aside. Zuma hosted Malema for tea on Friday. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 [In Pictures]: The CIC @Julius_S_Malema at the Former President of South Africa, Jacob Zuma’s Homestead in Nkandla, having TEA. pic.twitter.com/1JzFNz2lIw